&lt;p data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;413&quot;&gt;ENSCO RAIL&#39;s Division designs, develops and manufactures precision, high speed, real-time track inspection systems for the national and international railway market. We are seeking a skilled Field Service Engineer to join our service group, to provide installation, test, debug and repair of complex railway-vehicle-based electro-mechanical inertial and optical based data acquisition systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;415&quot; data-end=&quot;471&quot;&gt;Responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;472&quot; data-end=&quot;970&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;472&quot; data-end=&quot;647&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;474&quot; data-end=&quot;647&quot;&gt;Field service, troubleshooting, maintenance and repair of equipment on railway vehicles at various domestic and international customer sites, as well as in our facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;648&quot; data-end=&quot;738&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;650&quot; data-end=&quot;738&quot;&gt;Installation, calibration and testing of track inspection systems on railway vehicles.&lt;/p&gt;
