&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years of relevant experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in data acquisition and test development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced skills in digital signal processing, data processing, geophysical modeling, and interpretation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience in algorithm development and machine learning applications for geophysical data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with multiple sensor types and techniques including seismic, acoustic, acceleration, electromagnetic, and ground-penetrating radar (GPR) sensors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience analyzing large, multimodal datasets from a variety of sensors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in scientific programming languages such as MATLAB, Python, R, or C/C++&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in developing test procedures and writing technical reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in outdoor field environments and remote testing locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to document field activities, equipment status, and test procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent time management and organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively in dynamic team environments and achieve overall program objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift and carry equipment weighing 50+ lbs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be willing to travel (10-15%) and perform field work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work flexible hours when supporting field operations or testing activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent oral and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a current SECRET security clearance with the ability to obtain and maintain TOP SECRET/SCI, for which you must be a U.S. citizen. You will not be considered for this position if you do not meet this requirement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
