&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;ENSCO is seeking a Target Digital Network Analyst (TDNA) to support the U.S. Army Space and Missile Defense Command (USASMDC) Intelligence Directorate in Colorado Springs, Colorado.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The selected candidate will support the USASMDC Signals Intelligence Branch and the U.S. Army Space Theater Technical Control and Analysis Element (Sp-TCAE) by conducting digital network analysis in support of Signals Intelligence (SIGINT), technical SIGINT (TECHSIGINT),&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Processing, Exploitation, and Dissemination (PED), and target development activities.&lt;br&gt;- Conduct Target Digital Network Analysis in support of operational intelligence missions.&lt;br&gt;- Analyze digital communications networks and associated infrastructure.&lt;br&gt;- Assist in identifying network relationships and communication patterns.&lt;br&gt;- Support SIGINT and TECHSIGINT exploitation activities.&lt;br&gt;- Participate in Processing, Exploitation, and Dissemination (PED) operations.&lt;br&gt;- Support target development and intelligence production.&lt;br&gt;- Correlate digital network intelligence with SIGINT, GEOINT, and All Source Intelligence.&lt;br&gt;- Produce intelligence reports, graphics, and analytical products.&lt;br&gt;- Maintain intelligence databases and analytical records.&lt;br&gt;- Support operational planning and intelligence briefings.&lt;br&gt;- Support real world crisis and contingency operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications Required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#39;- Bachelor&#39;s degree in Intelligence, Computer Science, Cybersecurity, Information Systems, Engineering, or related field, or equivalent experience, plus 5 years of experience supporting Target Digital Network Analysis or related intelligence disciplines.&lt;br&gt;- Experience supporting SIGINT and PED operations.&lt;br&gt;- Experience conducting digital network analysis for intelligence production.&lt;br&gt;- Experience supporting military targeting operations.&lt;br&gt;- Strong analytical and technical problem-solving skills.&lt;br&gt;- Excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;br&gt;- Active TS/SCI clearance for which you must be a US citizen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications Desired&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#39;- Army Military Intelligence experience.&lt;br&gt;- Familiarity with Target Digital Network Analysis concepts.&lt;br&gt;- Experience supporting SIGINT or PED operations.&lt;br&gt;- Experience with intelligence databases and analytical tools.&lt;br&gt;- Basic knowledge of network protocols and communications.&lt;br&gt;- Experience supporting targeting or operational planning.&lt;br&gt;- Experience integrating SIGINT with GEOINT and All Source Intelligence.&lt;br&gt;- NSA, INSCOM, or Combatant Command experience.&lt;br&gt;- Familiarity with cyber-enabled intelligence operations.&lt;br&gt;- Network+&lt;br&gt;- Security+&lt;br&gt;- Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;4266&quot; data-end=&quot;4294&quot;&gt;Required Certifications: &lt;/strong&gt;None&lt;br data-start=&quot;4314&quot; data-end=&quot;4317&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;4317&quot; data-end=&quot;4345&quot;&gt;

